Looks mostly like swapping to me. JVMs can use a signficant amount
of memory beyond the &#39;heap&#39; space -- we&#39;ve seen hundreds of megabytes
more, especially with long-running and multi-threaded applications.

The &#39;nice&#39; CPU figures below are also a little suspicious. If you
didn&#39;t run your JVMs niced, then something else was moderately busy
at that time, perhaps doing disk I/O.

- Gordon @ IA

